msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 44: After receiving his resignation, the Agency asked Bill to reconsider his decision, and as part of an inducement package, sent him to the Middle East for several months as a special consultant to the F...
#: paragraph:44,sentence:205
msgid "He said, in retrospect, that his Middle East trip was the most marvelous of his life."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 44: After receiving his resignation, the Agency asked Bill to reconsider his decision, and as part of an inducement package, sent him to the Middle East for several months as a special consultant to the F...
#: paragraph:44,sentence:206
msgid "After returning, he was generously promised a range of positions with the Agency, not necessarily in Washington, and felt some obligation to stay on for a while."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 44: After receiving his resignation, the Agency asked Bill to reconsider his decision, and as part of an inducement package, sent him to the Middle East for several months as a special consultant to the F...
#: paragraph:44,sentence:207
msgid "He continued with the CIA until the summer of 1954, then was impelled to move on."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 45: Since he had been drawn to New York for some years, Bill thought the next obvious step was actually to apply for work there, which he did at the New York Unemployment Service Psychological Placement B...
#: paragraph:45,sentence:208
msgid "Since he had been drawn to New York for some years, Bill thought the next obvious step was actually to apply for work there, which he did at the New York Unemployment Service Psychological Placement Bureau."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 45: Since he had been drawn to New York for some years, Bill thought the next obvious step was actually to apply for work there, which he did at the New York Unemployment Service Psychological Placement B...
#: paragraph:45,sentence:209
msgid "Although he indicated he wanted to live in the city, the head of the service said, “They want you in Hartford [CT]."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 45: Since he had been drawn to New York for some years, Bill thought the next obvious step was actually to apply for work there, which he did at the New York Unemployment Service Psychological Placement B...
#: paragraph:45,sentence:210
msgid "That’s where you have to go, the Institute of Living.”[34] He sent Bill immediately to the institute, an adjunct of the Hartford Hospital, one of the first mental health centers in the country and then the largest psychiatric hospital in the United States."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 45: Since he had been drawn to New York for some years, Bill thought the next obvious step was actually to apply for work there, which he did at the New York Unemployment Service Psychological Placement B...
#: paragraph:45,sentence:211
msgid "There is now reason to believe that, unknown to Bill at the time, the CIA had a covert hand in steering him in that direction, and at the ripe old age of thirty-one, he was hired as director of clinical psychology."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 45: Since he had been drawn to New York for some years, Bill thought the next obvious step was actually to apply for work there, which he did at the New York Unemployment Service Psychological Placement B...
#: paragraph:45,sentence:212
msgid "Although many well-known people were doing interesting things at the institute, he felt it was not quite his place; it was not New York."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 45: Since he had been drawn to New York for some years, Bill thought the next obvious step was actually to apply for work there, which he did at the New York Unemployment Service Psychological Placement B...
#: paragraph:45,sentence:213
msgid "He did leave his imprint there, however, and according to the 1956 annual report, the Division of Clinical Psychology under Bill’s direction expanded its research to include “better diagnosis of organic pathology through psychological tests, the use of projective techniques in predicting aggressive behavior, and appraising changes resulting from psychotherapy.”[35] This research was indeed a continuation of his work with the PAS, and John Gittinger was involved with its funding."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 46: During Bill’s short tenure at the institute, Dr. Harold Wolff, a world-famous neurologist, one of the founders of psychosomatic medicine, and chairman of the Neurology Department at Cornell University...
#: paragraph:46,sentence:214
msgid "During Bill’s short tenure at the institute, Dr. Harold Wolff, a world-famous neurologist, one of the founders of psychosomatic medicine, and chairman of the Neurology Department at Cornell University Medical Center in New York, invited Bill to join him."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 46: During Bill’s short tenure at the institute, Dr. Harold Wolff, a world-famous neurologist, one of the founders of psychosomatic medicine, and chairman of the Neurology Department at Cornell University...
#: paragraph:46,sentence:215
msgid "Bill used to joke that if his qualification for employment at Michael Reese Hospital had been to know nothing about the Rorschach test, his qualifications for the Cornell position were singular."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 46: During Bill’s short tenure at the institute, Dr. Harold Wolff, a world-famous neurologist, one of the founders of psychosomatic medicine, and chairman of the Neurology Department at Cornell University...
#: paragraph:46,sentence:216
msgid "Not only was his work in Washington germane to the Cornell program, he was the only clinical psychologist around with top secret security clearance and trained in neurophysiology."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 46: During Bill’s short tenure at the institute, Dr. Harold Wolff, a world-famous neurologist, one of the founders of psychosomatic medicine, and chairman of the Neurology Department at Cornell University...
#: paragraph:46,sentence:217
msgid "Dr. Wolff had been offered the opportunity to do cross-cultural studies funded by the CIA and he hired Bill as head of the psychological research program."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 46: During Bill’s short tenure at the institute, Dr. Harold Wolff, a world-famous neurologist, one of the founders of psychosomatic medicine, and chairman of the Neurology Department at Cornell University...
#: paragraph:46,sentence:218
msgid "Part of Bill’s job was to revise the PAS for use with foreign cultures, particularly the Chinese."
msgstr ""

#. Paragraph 46: During Bill’s short tenure at the institute, Dr. Harold Wolff, a world-famous neurologist, one of the founders of psychosomatic medicine, and chairman of the Neurology Department at Cornell University...
#: paragraph:46,sentence:219
msgid "In addition to his research work there, which was primary, he also became first an instructor and soon thereafter an assistant professor of psychology in the Department of Psychiatry."
msgstr ""

